  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nCurrently the width of StatusMenu is fixed what is problematic when content is dynamic and also for translations:\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2023-06-12 12-38-03](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/20650004/a5126c9f-b5a2-4cb3-ade9-6cd3bb7abaec)\r\n\r\nWhile having it fixed, `SortableTokenHoldersPanel.qml` can be adjusted according to the design: \r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?type=design&node-id=29473-626171&t=Rw4edL9LegNa9ez6-0\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?type=design&node-id=29456-601850&t=Rw4edL9LegNa9ez6-0\r\n\r\n<!-- Provide a short description describing the problem you are experiencing. -->\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\nUse `StatusMenu` with long item text.\r\n<!-- example: step 1. do X step 2. do Y etc.. -->\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n`StatusMenu` width should adapt to the width of items\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n`StatusMenu` width is fixed, leading to elision for longer texts.\r\n\r\n",
